{"questionId":"32463998","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Juan uses a different transformation, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi></math>, defined by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">To create his animation, he repeatedly transforms an object by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi></math>. After many transformations, he notices that all points, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, on the object tend towards a single point, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, such that</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mi>a</mi></msup><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>p</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>q</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>20</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32463998","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.6f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find pq, where p, q ∈ℝ.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maxim